        "\ud83d\udd2c HIDDEN GEOMETRY \u2014 WIDE VALLEY \u2014 World Tracing backend (HONEST WEAK CASE)\n\nSweep 2026-07-09: neither backend truly fires here \u2014 WT registers\n(0.139) but predicts hidden surfaces on only ~2% of the band; LaRI\nmisregisters (0.597). With fill_gaps the sparse predictions still\ndiffuse into a usable near-field surface, but treat this scene as\n'know when the method barely fires' \u2014 the report tells you.\n\nARCHITECTURE \u2014 MASK-MEMBERSHIP X-RAY (v2, calibrated 2026-07-09):\n1. ONE solve + ONE shared DA3 depth (solved focal).\n2. BASE: AtlasDeriveReliefMesh on the ORIGINAL depth + its\n   projection_backdrop \u2014 guarantees no black at camera view.\n3. RESTRICT: AtlasDepthLayerMask (manual, far_pct = nearest occluders)\n   feeds the \ud83d\udd2c node's restrict_mask.\n4. \ud83d\udd2c X-RAY: predicts per-ray hidden surfaces, then makes them COHERENT \u2014\n   fill_gaps diffuses the fragmented predictions into ONE surface across\n   the restrict region and smooth_px gaussian-smooths the seams (both\n   essential: fragmented/steppy depth shreds the layer mesh via the\n   world-edge check, IMMUNE to depth_edge_rel \u2014 measured).\n5. FOREGROUND layer: a matted AtlasCleanPlateLayer on the ORIGINAL\n   photo/depth (band = the restrict range, embed_matte + skirts,\n   priority 10) cleanly covers the occluders' own silhouettes at camera\n   view. Without it, base-mesh tears at silhouettes let the X-ray's\n   INPAINTED plate peek through at camera view (artist-caught: inpaint\n   content visible where the normal image should cover).\n6. THE X-RAY LAYER: AtlasCleanPlateLayer with NO depth band at all\n   (manual, far uncapped \u2014 a depth split cannot hold near-field hidden\n   geometry; measured: every split loses 76-97% of predictions). Its\n   geometry region = hidden_mask via GrowMask(32) \u2192 InvertMask \u2192\n   exclude_mask; its PAINT = the \ud83d\udd2c paint_matte (only where the hidden\n   surface is genuinely behind a nearer occluder \u2014 see-through gaps\n   discard in the shader and show the base mesh's real far content).\n7. PLATE: LaMa inpaints the occluders out (hidden_mask grown 48px), so\n   reveals get real pixels. Swap LanPaint/FLUX for hero shots.\n8. Viewport: \ud83d\udcfd Project on; \ud83e\ude7b X-ray toggles the provenance tint (red =\n   LaRI / blue = World Tracing, = the paint matte); dolly demo via\n   \ud83c\udfa5 Camera Path \u2192 Dolly In \u2192 \u23fa Bake \u2192 VideoCombine Plus mp4; unmute\n   the USD node after baking.\n\n\ud83d\udd2c EXPERIMENTAL / RESEARCH-ONLY. LaRI: unlicensed upstream (clone +\nlari_path / ATLAS_LARI_PATH). World Tracing: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0, HF-gated\ncheckpoint (clone + wt_path / ATLAS_WT_PATH + huggingface login). Seeds\nship PINNED (control_after_generate=fixed) \u2014 WT is diffusion; a\nrandomized seed re-rolls the hidden geometry every queue. See INSTALL.md\n+ docs/dev/hidden_geometry_training_free_research.md."
      ],
      "title": "README"
    }
